URL: https://github.com/apache/arrow/pull/6324#issuecomment-586980376


   > Does this error relate to this change?
   
   Yes, it does. As mentioned in the PR message, unity builds can lead to C++ namespace resolution issues. Let's say you have two different files:
   
   ```c++
   // a.cpp
   
   namespace arrow {
   namespace io {
   namespace internal {
   
   void SomeFunction();
   }
   }
   }
   ```
   
   ```c++
   // b.cpp
   
   namespace arrow {
   namespace io {
   using internal::OtherFunction;
   }
   }
   ```
   
   If `b.cpp` is compiled separately, `internal::OtherFunction` can refer to `::arrow::internal::OtherFunction`. But if `a.cpp` and `b.cpp` are concatenated together, then `internal::OtherFunction` will refer to `::arrow::io::internal::OtherFunction` which may not exist.


